wikipedia_page.main: George James Ross (1 December 1877 – 27 August 1945) was a British gymnast who competed in the 1908 and 1912 Olympic Games.As a member of the British team in 1908, he finished eighth in the team competition. He was part of the British team which won the bronze medal in the gymnastics men's team, in the European system event in 1912.
